1
00:01:40,530 --> 00:01:44,210
[A Moment But Forever]

2
00:01:45,100 --> 00:01:47,220
[Episode 31]

3
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:49,950
Watch your step.

4
00:01:54,590 --> 00:01:55,920
In the Fragrant Grove,

5
00:01:56,280 --> 00:01:57,560
there's a friend of mine

6
00:01:58,229 --> 00:02:00,000
who specializes in spatial barrier techniques.

7
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:01,640
We can take shelter at her place

8
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:02,430
for a while.

9
00:02:08,310 --> 00:02:09,120
Stop hiding.

10
00:02:09,750 --> 00:02:10,560
Come out now.

11
00:02:15,190 --> 00:02:16,430
If you don't,

12
00:02:16,750 --> 00:02:17,750
I'll tear your place

13
00:02:17,750 --> 00:02:18,710
down.

14
00:02:26,710 --> 00:02:29,270
[Youhu Clan, Curly]

15
00:02:37,190 --> 00:02:39,400
Yuanzhong, what brings you here?

16
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:41,710
We came as guests,

17
00:02:42,030 --> 00:02:43,360
and yet you don't even offer us tea?

18
00:03:05,960 --> 00:03:06,750
Tanyin,

19
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:09,030
this is my childhood friend.

20
00:03:11,470 --> 00:03:12,590
Just an acquaintance.

21
00:03:13,240 --> 00:03:14,520
You can call her Curly.

22
00:03:14,920 --> 00:03:16,079
She was born with curly fur.

23
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:17,240
When she was little,

24
00:03:17,870 --> 00:03:19,150
she once stole Dingxu's Heaven-Turning Seal

25
00:03:19,590 --> 00:03:21,280
just to straighten her fur

26
00:03:21,480 --> 00:03:22,950
and almost got crushed to death by it.

27
00:03:23,750 --> 00:03:25,150
I didn't steal it. I just borrowed it.

28
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:30,470
Why did you laugh?

29
00:03:32,520 --> 00:03:33,870
I laughed because it was funny.

30
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:35,280
Is laughing

31
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:36,960
not allowed here?

32
00:03:39,710 --> 00:03:41,560
After that, she caused some trouble

33
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:43,870
and couldn't stay in the clan anymore.

34
00:03:44,310 --> 00:03:45,840
I gave her the Fragrant Grove

35
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:47,470
so she'd have a place to live.

36
00:03:48,079 --> 00:03:49,120
She once told me

37
00:03:49,710 --> 00:03:50,840
she owed me a favor.

38
00:03:51,560 --> 00:03:52,710
She promised to repay me no matter what,

39
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:54,030
even if it meant going through

40
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:55,400
extreme challenges.

41
00:03:56,190 --> 00:03:57,000
Now,

42
00:03:57,630 --> 00:03:59,190
it's time for her to make good on that promise.

43
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:00,680
So that's why

44
00:04:00,680 --> 00:04:01,750
you asked me to bring you here?

45
00:04:03,590 --> 00:04:04,590
Curly's other spells

46
00:04:04,590 --> 00:04:05,590
are mediocre at best,

47
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:07,710
but when it comes to spatial barrier techniques,

48
00:04:08,030 --> 00:04:09,310
she is exceptionally skilled.

49
00:04:09,590 --> 00:04:11,150
When she was a kid and got into trouble,

50
00:04:11,280 --> 00:04:12,840
she'd always hide,

51
00:04:13,150 --> 00:04:14,240
and no one could find her.

52
00:04:14,710 --> 00:04:15,960
She really had some skills.

53
00:04:16,250 --> 00:04:17,370
What does that mean?

54
00:04:18,310 --> 00:04:19,269
Are you here to take my life?

55
00:04:20,430 --> 00:04:21,680
Not to take your life.

56
00:04:22,270 --> 00:04:23,920
Just to stay for a few days.

57
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:25,430
That's basically the same as taking my life!

58
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:27,040
This place is so cramped,

59
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:28,040
with three people living here,

60
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:29,560
constantly bumping into each other.

61
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:30,840
How could we possibly live like that?

62
00:04:31,190 --> 00:04:32,000
What?

63
00:04:33,430 --> 00:04:34,560
We can't stay?

64
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:35,470
No.

65
00:04:40,190 --> 00:04:42,480
I can tell you're hurt,

66
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:44,120
so you must be going through something.

67
00:04:44,250 --> 00:04:45,370
But you're more than

68
00:04:45,480 --> 00:04:47,310
capable of

69
00:04:47,430 --> 00:04:48,750
finding a safe spot.

70
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:49,600
Why must you...

71
00:04:49,980 --> 00:04:52,610
Why must you put someone else in a tough spot?

72
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:53,560
Right?

73
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:54,830
Since I'm here,

74
00:04:55,390 --> 00:04:56,920
I have my reasons.

75
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:58,190
I don't care about your reasons!

76
00:04:58,190 --> 00:04:59,600
You simply can't stay here.

77
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:01,160
What about the favor you owe me?

78
00:05:01,310 --> 00:05:02,310
I'd go through

79
00:05:02,310 --> 00:05:03,600
any extreme task for you,

80
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:05,240
but you can't stay here!

81
00:05:05,750 --> 00:05:06,920
You know me.

82
00:05:06,980 --> 00:05:08,370
I just can't tolerate it.

83
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:14,510
Alright.

84
00:05:15,870 --> 00:05:17,120
Then we have no choice

85
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:19,510
but to return to Fangwai Mountain.

86
00:05:22,390 --> 00:05:23,190
Oh, by the way,

87
00:05:23,310 --> 00:05:24,510
your three elder sisters

88
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:26,070
miss you very much,

89
00:05:26,240 --> 00:05:27,430
especially your second sister.

90
00:05:27,630 --> 00:05:28,870
She's been longing to see you.

91
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:30,070
Your second sister

92
00:05:30,270 --> 00:05:31,870
is really blessed.

93
00:05:32,270 --> 00:05:34,630
She has a happy marriage and a flourishing family.

94
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:36,310
She now has eight children.

95
00:05:36,720 --> 00:05:38,870
The youngest still hasn't mastered transformation.

96
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:40,800
If they find out you're here

97
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:42,360
and all come to visit,

98
00:05:42,570 --> 00:05:43,770
the Fragrant Grove

99
00:05:44,430 --> 00:05:45,510
will be bustling.

100
00:05:48,510 --> 00:05:49,310
Wait!

101
00:05:52,830 --> 00:05:54,159
If you want to stay here,

102
00:05:54,159 --> 00:05:55,720
you'll have to follow my rules.

103
00:05:56,120 --> 00:05:57,270
You're just temporary guests here,

104
00:05:57,270 --> 00:05:58,560
not the owners.

105
00:05:58,680 --> 00:05:59,680
You'll have to take care of

106
00:05:59,680 --> 00:06:00,830
your own food, clothes, shelter, and transport.

107
00:06:00,830 --> 00:06:02,040
Don't expect me to serve you.

108
00:06:02,430 --> 00:06:04,240
I'm not in the habit of waiting on anyone.

109
00:06:05,120 --> 00:06:05,920
Oh, by the way,

110
00:06:05,950 --> 00:06:07,360
you're Yuanzhong's servant girl, right?

111
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:08,920
Take good care of him

112
00:06:08,980 --> 00:06:10,740
and make sure he leaves as soon as possible.

113
00:06:11,160 --> 00:06:12,720
Is this your kitchen?

114
00:06:13,750 --> 00:06:14,560
Yes.

115
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:17,560
It's very clean.

116
00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:22,270
Even the stove is spotless.

117
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:25,120
Do you never cook with fire?

118
00:06:25,740 --> 00:06:27,300
Lighting a fire to cook is too troublesome,

119
00:06:27,480 --> 00:06:29,190
and the dust is hard to clean.

120
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:31,000
I always eat fresh fruits

121
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:31,920
and raw food.

122
00:06:32,390 --> 00:06:33,750
We prefer cooked food

123
00:06:33,920 --> 00:06:34,720
and hot meals.

124
00:06:41,310 --> 00:06:42,560
These are all medicinal herbs.

125
00:06:42,920 --> 00:06:43,800
There's so much of it.

126
00:06:44,190 --> 00:06:45,000
Really?

127
00:06:46,430 --> 00:06:48,310
I thought it was just some wild greens.

128
00:06:48,480 --> 00:06:50,120
I gathered them from the forest.

129
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:51,310
They taste awful.

130
00:06:51,310 --> 00:06:52,120
Extremely bitter.

131
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:54,950
Yuanzhong is seriously injured;

132
00:06:54,980 --> 00:06:56,190
he needs medicine to recover.

133
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:57,270
Do you have any tools

134
00:06:57,270 --> 00:06:58,680
for decocting herbs?

135
00:06:59,010 --> 00:07:00,040
I wasn't done speaking yet.

136
00:07:00,190 --> 00:07:00,950
Well,

137
00:07:00,950 --> 00:07:02,830
the two rooms on the east side are for you.

138
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:04,920
That loft is my bedroom.

139
00:07:05,160 --> 00:07:06,310
I usually

140
00:07:06,310 --> 00:07:07,830
eat, rest,

141
00:07:07,830 --> 00:07:10,070
read, train, and meditate there.

142
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:11,870
All of that is important to me.

143
00:07:12,510 --> 00:07:14,390
If you have nothing urgent, don't disturb me.

144
00:07:14,830 --> 00:07:16,950
Even if you do, it's best not to.

145
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:18,070
So, if we

146
00:07:18,070 --> 00:07:19,120
ever need to find you,

147
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:20,160
what should we do?

148
00:07:20,160 --> 00:07:21,160
Write a letter.

149
00:07:22,270 --> 00:07:23,070
See that mailbox

150
00:07:23,070 --> 00:07:24,680
in the courtyard?

151
00:07:24,870 --> 00:07:26,000
If you need something,

152
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,560
just put a letter in there.

153
00:07:27,560 --> 00:07:29,000
I'll check it once a day at 7 p.m.

154
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:30,040
If I need anything,

155
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:31,720
I'll contact you the same way.

156
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:35,070
Looks like you won't be leaving

157
00:07:35,070 --> 00:07:36,920
in just a few days, huh?

158
00:07:37,310 --> 00:07:38,870
Then let's set some rules now.

159
00:07:39,070 --> 00:07:40,340
No one disturbs anyone,

160
00:07:40,480 --> 00:07:41,510
and we each keep to ourselves.

161
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:42,510
Sounds good?

162
00:07:50,540 --> 00:07:52,060
I wasn't finished talking.

163
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:55,070
Let me tell you about

164
00:07:55,070 --> 00:07:56,800
my daily routine.

165
00:07:57,190 --> 00:07:58,750
As long as we avoid

166
00:07:58,870 --> 00:08:00,390
using the same space

167
00:08:00,390 --> 00:08:01,390
for the same things

168
00:08:01,390 --> 00:08:02,510
at the same time,

169
00:08:02,510 --> 00:08:03,560
we won't run into each other

170
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:05,270
or cause any trouble.

171
00:08:05,560 --> 00:08:07,600
I usually wake up at 9 a.m.,

172
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:08,630
wash up at 10:15 a.m.,

173
00:08:08,630 --> 00:08:09,680
eat at 10:45 a.m.,

174
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:10,950
and train at noon.

175
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:11,870
Are you done yet?

176
00:08:11,870 --> 00:08:12,480
Not yet.

177
00:08:12,480 --> 00:08:13,430
That was just the fifth rule.

178
00:08:13,430 --> 00:08:14,560
There's still the sixth.

179
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:16,230
This place originally belonged to Yuanzhong, didn't it?

180
00:08:16,820 --> 00:08:17,620
Yes.

181
00:08:19,390 --> 00:08:20,750
But now I live here,

182
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:21,950
so it's mine.

183
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:25,920
We had no choice but to come here,

184
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:27,270
but we won't stay long.

185
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:28,750
I'll do my best

186
00:08:28,750 --> 00:08:30,000
to follow your rules,

187
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:31,310
but if I can't,

188
00:08:31,330 --> 00:08:32,539
I hope you can be understanding.

189
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:35,720
I haven't finished it yet!

190
00:08:36,030 --> 00:08:36,840
Write it down.

191
00:08:39,480 --> 00:08:40,929
I haven't mentioned the sixth rule yet.

192
00:08:51,480 --> 00:08:53,030
Curly isn't a bad person.

193
00:08:53,750 --> 00:08:55,390
She's just a little reclusive.

194
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:56,870
It's not a big deal.

195
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:00,790
Are you still bothered by what happened in Yandu?

196
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:03,840
I'm not upset.

197
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:05,670
I just don't get it.

198
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:07,120
Don't get it?

199
00:09:08,870 --> 00:09:10,120
You're not a villain,

200
00:09:10,630 --> 00:09:12,270
and you haven't hurt anyone.

201
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:13,320
Why did they

202
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:14,360
treat you like that?

203
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:16,230
Humans are treacherous,

204
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:18,150
and easily swayed by the crowd.

205
00:09:18,630 --> 00:09:20,630
And when divine forces

206
00:09:20,630 --> 00:09:21,720
come into play,

207
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:25,120
their choices seem inevitable.

208
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:34,960
This shouldn't have happened.

209
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:38,510
You're too clever

210
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:40,440
to not understand this.

211
00:09:41,030 --> 00:09:42,120
You just feel that...

212
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:43,550
I feel sorry for you.

213
00:09:43,670 --> 00:09:45,200
I feel that you are treated unfairly.

214
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:47,150
Leaving aside the War Demons,

215
00:09:47,150 --> 00:09:48,720
at the very least, the humans and the Youhu Clan

216
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:50,390
should've been grateful to you.

217
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:52,270
They should have remembered your kindness.

218
00:09:52,630 --> 00:09:54,270
It shouldn't have turned out this way.

219
00:10:04,550 --> 00:10:05,750
Throughout this long journey of escape,

220
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:07,440
you've endured so much.

221
00:10:08,030 --> 00:10:09,870
You've mentioned it countless times already.

222
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,000
I must say it again.

223
00:10:12,030 --> 00:10:14,120
No matter how many times I say it, it's never enough.

224
00:10:15,030 --> 00:10:16,150
Actually, over the past few days,

225
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:18,630
I wasn't entirely unconscious.

226
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:21,120
I woke up a few times,

227
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:22,240
feeling disoriented and confused.

228
00:10:23,720 --> 00:10:24,720
Each time I woke up,

229
00:10:25,440 --> 00:10:26,960
I could hear your voice.

230
00:10:27,510 --> 00:10:28,480
I thought to myself,

231
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:32,600
heaven hasn't been too harsh with me.

232
00:10:33,790 --> 00:10:35,280
At least I met you.

233
00:10:40,750 --> 00:10:41,670
There's something

234
00:10:41,670 --> 00:10:42,840
I haven't told you.

235
00:10:43,510 --> 00:10:44,320
Actually, back then,

236
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:45,840
what you saw in my sea of consciousness

237
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:48,030
wasn't the whole picture.

238
00:10:48,710 --> 00:10:49,950
They call me the demon,

239
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:52,320
and that's not entirely untrue.

240
00:10:53,390 --> 00:10:54,910
During the forty years I was locked away,

241
00:10:55,740 --> 00:10:57,510
I had a thought.

242
00:10:58,410 --> 00:11:01,290
I believed the world was full of sin,

243
00:11:01,910 --> 00:11:03,030
that human nature was inherently evil.

244
00:11:03,630 --> 00:11:04,600
Always hungry, seeking to be filled;

245
00:11:05,040 --> 00:11:06,070
when cold, yearning for warmth;

246
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:08,630
when warm, craving pride, luxury, and indulgence;

247
00:11:08,910 --> 00:11:10,000
always desiring more.

248
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:11,750
So,

249
00:11:12,510 --> 00:11:14,320
I wanted to use the Divine Left Hand as a sacrifice

250
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:16,670
to pass judgment on all the sins in this world.

251
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:18,670
Those who bore the Five Sins

252
00:11:19,270 --> 00:11:21,720
would be consumed by Heavenly Fire.

253
00:11:23,200 --> 00:11:26,390
I believed that, given how corrupt the world was,

254
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:28,440
once the judgment was made,

255
00:11:29,490 --> 00:11:31,260
everything would be purified and transformed into a clear, bright place.

256
00:11:32,750 --> 00:11:34,550
From the moment I was freed,

257
00:11:35,360 --> 00:11:37,200
I was resolute in carrying out this plan.

258
00:11:38,440 --> 00:11:40,360
I thought, since the world had wronged me,

259
00:11:41,630 --> 00:11:43,150
I would repay its evil with vengeance on all.

260
00:11:45,030 --> 00:11:45,840
But,

261
00:11:46,630 --> 00:11:48,200
fate had me meet you.

262
00:11:50,510 --> 00:11:51,320
Ji Tanyin,

263
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:54,720
you have always treated me with genuine sincerity,

264
00:11:55,550 --> 00:11:56,590
never pretending,

265
00:11:58,040 --> 00:11:59,680
and saving me from danger over and over again.

266
00:12:00,390 --> 00:12:01,790
At first, I doubted you.

267
00:12:03,080 --> 00:12:04,440
I couldn't believe someone like you

268
00:12:04,670 --> 00:12:06,240
could exist in this world.

269
00:12:06,910 --> 00:12:08,360
And I couldn't believe that heaven

270
00:12:09,790 --> 00:12:11,750
would show any favor to someone like me.

271
00:12:14,510 --> 00:12:15,360
But gradually,

272
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:18,240
I started to like you.

273
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:21,360
My heart became attached,

274
00:12:22,150 --> 00:12:23,150
and I felt a sense of longing.

275
00:12:24,750 --> 00:12:25,550
I was afraid,

276
00:12:26,910 --> 00:12:28,220
afraid that I might falter.

277
00:12:29,230 --> 00:12:31,200
So, when we were at Orange Lake and Yandu,

278
00:12:32,110 --> 00:12:33,120
I pushed you away

279
00:12:34,660 --> 00:12:36,420
because I was afraid that, because of you,

280
00:12:37,320 --> 00:12:38,840
I would lose myself.

281
00:12:48,910 --> 00:12:50,030
In the battle at Yandu,

282
00:12:51,390 --> 00:12:52,960
even though the whole world criticized me,

283
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:54,560
even though I was cornered,

284
00:12:55,670 --> 00:12:57,030
I never regretted it.

285
00:12:58,080 --> 00:12:59,000
When you gain something,

286
00:12:59,790 --> 00:13:01,030
you will inevitably lose something.

